    <text>
        <body>
            
            <div1 type="letter">
                
                <pb facs="nei.j4a.27b.22-25_0001"/>
                
                <note type="curatorial">Neihardt Collection
                    7</note>
                
                <fw type="curatorial">22</fw>
                
                <opener>
                    <dateline>
                        Aug. 5, 59
                        2538 Wabash.
                        <hi rend="caps">K.C.</hi> Mo.,
                    </dateline>
                    
                    Mr. <hi rend="caps">J.G.</hi> Neihardt.
                    <salute>Kind sir: &#8212;</salute>
                </opener>
                <p>Your letter thrilled me so, until I take time off, to answer it. Much oblige sir, for showing so much graditude<sic>gratitude</sic>, and appreciation for a job I spent many days in doing I am (71) seventy one years old I purchased wife and I your old home stead (15) fifteen years ago in a very run down condition, (8) eight years ago we finished paying for said property and that is when our reconstruction era began, in front yard we have spent over ($1500) fifteen hundred dollars for trees, &amp; whatnots I rebuild the old front porch, I do not know whether you looked at back yard or not but I believe it is more attractive than front yard, their<sic>there</sic> is a patio, a (2) two
                
                <pb facs="nei.j4a.27b.22-25_0002"/>
                
                <fw type="curatorial">23</fw>
                <fw type="authorial">-2-</fw>
                
                    car garage &#8212; a roof garden on top of garage with flowers growing in giant boxes, a gold fish<sic>goldfish</sic> pond in center of back yard a (53) fifty three ft. 3 inches grape, <unclear>orbar<sic>arbor</sic></unclear> which I rebuilt this spring and painted it in fact I used this spring (45) forty five gallons of paint 14 <unclear>sts</unclear>, of paint thinner (6) six cans of putty on property my kind sir, I painted everything that was paintable (smiles) &amp; the strange thing about this matter, I did all this work by myself without any help whatsoever And I hope you remember I am (71) seventy one years old, when this warm weather outside subsides I shall go inside and beautify the entire inside new wallpaper sanded floors new rugs &amp; every thing (8) eight years ago, this was the worst looking home in city, hard work &amp; quite a lot of money has turned the <hi rend="underline">Ugly Duckling</hi> into a <hi rend="underline">beautiful Swan</hi> (smiles)</p>
                
                <p>One of my neighbors said you took pictures of this place, being kind enough to write me
                
                <pb facs="nei.j4a.27b.22-25_0003"/>
                    
                <fw type="curatorial">24</fw>
                <fw type="authorial">-3-</fw>
                
                    would you be kind enough to first send me a photo of yourself so I can hang it in my study and, also a picture of the Swan that was once an Ugly Duckling</p>
                    
                <p>Thanking you again for your thoughtfulness and, when time will permit me I shall look you up sir;&#8212; in Who's Who</p>
                
                <p>I am your brother in Christ Jesus.</p>
                
                <p>I would like to put a roof on garage so if you would like to contribute to this cause, it will cost ($35.00) thirty five dollars.</p>
                
                <p>it will be highly appreciated</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>Rev. P.D. Harris</signed>
                </closer>
                
                <postscript>
                    <opener><hi rend="caps">P.S.</hi></opener> <p>Your letter shall as it is go into my (63) sixty three years Diary</p>
                </postscript>
                
            </div1>
            
            
            <div1 type="envelope">
                
                <pb facs="nei.j4a.27b.22-25_0004"/>
                
                <ab type="return">
                    <hi rend="caps">AFTER FIVE DAYS RETURN TO</hi>
                        <lb/>
                    Rev. <hi rend="caps">P.D.</hi> Harris.
                    2538 Wabash
                    Kansas City Mo.,
                </ab>
                
                <ab type="postmark">
                    KANSAS CITY
                    AUG 6
                    7 PM
                    1959
                    5 MO.
                </ab>
                
                <ab type="address">
                    <address>
                        <addrLine>Mr. John G. Neihardt.</addrLine>
                            <addrLine>Route #7.</addrLine>
                                <addrLine>Columbia.</addrLine>
                                    <addrLine>Missouri.</addrLine>
                    </address>
                </ab>
                
            </div1>
